<blockquote>
  <p>The <code>application/json</code> works great in PHP to store an array or object
  data.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>I use this code to put data in JSON on <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/35738814/4058484"><em>Google Cloud Storage (GCS)</em></a> which is set <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/38866924/4058484">publically viewable</a>:</p>

<pre><code>$context = stream_context_create([
    'gs' =&gt; [
        'acl'=&gt;'public-read', 
        'Content-Type' =&gt; 'application/json',
    ]
]);

file_put_contents(
    "gs://BUCKETNAME/FILENAME.json", 
    json_encode((object) $array), 
    false, 
    $context
);
</code></pre>

<p>To get back the data is straight forward:</p>

<pre><code>$data = json_decode(file_get_contents("gs://BUCKETNAME/FILENAME.json"));
</code></pre>
